NAME
     afasize - compute the state number of an alternating  finite
     state machine

SYNOPSIS
     afasize afa

     afasize < afa

DESCRIPTION
     afasize computes the number of states of  a  given  _a_f_a  and
     writes the result on the standard output.

     _a_f_a must conform to the Grail bit-wise format for  alternat-
     ing finite state machines.

EXAMPLES
          % cat bitafa1
          symbols: [a,b]
          states:  3
          finals:  5
          head: 7 4
          7 5
          7 1
          0 1
          3 1
          6 2
          7 3

          % afasize  bitafa1
          3

          %afasize < bitafa1
          3

          %cat bitafa1 |afasize
          3
          (Reg.).fi


